Research findings + implementation plan for tracking functions from
creation through changes to decommissioning.

Key findings:
- Existing code ontologies (CodeOntology, SEON) are OOP-centric, don't fit TS
- git log -L uses regex, not AST — misses 34% of TS functions
- AST parsing finds 100% of functions at all indent levels
- Blast radius model validated: lib/errors.ts → 6 files, session-pool → 44 files
- All required infrastructure exists (call graph parser, XTDB, QLever, decision log)

Architecture: post-commit git hook → AST parse changed files only → diff against
stored function registry → emit lifecycle events → calculate blast radius

5 phases, 9-14h total effort. Phases 1-2 work standalone without XTDB.
