From e2aafaa927b32132aa8b48f284155912aeed91db Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 21 Mar 2026 21:54:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/6] feat: add harness-native CI runner for Soft Serve
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A minimal CI/CD runner that integrates with the harness knowledge graph.
No external CI server needed — Soft Serve hooks trigger it, Docker runs
the containers, XTDB stores the results.

Components:
  ci-runner/runner.ts    — queue watcher, job executor, Docker orchestrator
  ci-runner/pipeline.ts  — reads .ci.yaml or auto-detects language:
                           TS→biome, Go→gofmt+vet+test, Rust→fmt+clippy,
                           Python→ruff+pytest, Elixir→format+credo+test
  ci-runner/recorder.ts  — writes ci_runs to XTDB as JSON-LD (code:CIRun)
  ci-runner/enqueue.sh   — writes job file to queue (called by hook)
  ci-runner/hooks/post-receive — Soft Serve hook, calls enqueue.sh

Automation layers (5 gates, none existed before):
  .vscode/settings.json  — Biome format-on-save + organize imports
  .githooks/pre-commit   — language-aware checks on staged files
  Taskfile.yml           — task check, task fmt, task ci:runner, task ci:run
  .github/workflows/     — GitHub Actions fallback (if not on Soft Serve)
  ci-runner/             — the real CI, async, Docker-native, XTDB-integrated

The flow:
  git push → Soft Serve post-receive → enqueue.sh → queue/job.json
  runner.ts → picks up job → checkout → detect language → Docker steps
  → results to XTDB → queryable via SPARQL on /graph page

Auto-detection tested: correctly identifies harness as TypeScript with
Biome, generates 'npm ci && npx biome ci .' step.
