From d6e85d09c0162f563c5e385364b457c8f89ea826 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 21 Mar 2026 21:59:12 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/6] fix: replace YAML pipeline config with JSON-LD
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The harness uses JSON-LD everywhere — decisions, test runs, events,
function lifecycle, call graphs. The CI pipeline config was the only
thing using YAML. That's an impedance mismatch: YAML needs a parser,
a schema validator, and a translation step before it enters the graph.

Changes:
- .ci.yaml → .ci.jsonld (pipeline config is native JSON-LD)
- Pipeline config stored as code:Pipeline in XTDB alongside run results
- recorder.ts uses shared JSONLD_CONTEXT from lib/jsonld/context.ts
- Auto-detected pipelines also emit JSON-LD (code:source: 'auto-detected')
- Runner passes pipelineJsonLd through to recorder for storage
- Removed unused randomUUID import from runner.ts

The pipeline config IS a graph node now. SPARQL queries like
'which repos use Biome?' work directly against code:Pipeline nodes
without any translation layer.
