Subject: [PATCH 6/6] =?UTF-8?q?docs:=20add=20RDF=20enforcement=20plan=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20kill=20string-soup=20JSON-LD?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The harness already has correct RDF tooling in xtdb-event-logger/rdf/:
N3.js DataFactory, namedNode(), literal(), triple(), JsonLdSerializer.
Every other module ignores it and hand-crafts JSON objects with string
keys. This is not RDF — it's string soup that happens to look like JSON-LD.

Problems with current approach:
- Typo 'schema:naem' silently creates a new predicate (no validation)
- Anyone can invent 'ev:whatever' (43 ev: predicates, no formal definition)
- Most ev: predicates duplicate standard vocabulary terms:
  ev:ts = prov:generatedAtTime, ev:status = schema:actionStatus,
  ev:agentName = prov:wasAssociatedWith, etc.
- No compile-time checking of predicate names

Solution: move xtdb-event-logger/rdf/ pattern to lib/rdf/ (shared),
define every predicate as a NamedNode constant in vocab.ts, provide
builder functions, ban raw JSONLD_CONTEXT imports via Biome.

Result: TypeScript compiler prevents inventing predicates. If
SCHEMA.naem doesn't exist in vocab.ts, you get a compile error.
The vocabulary IS the TypeScript type system.
